  "text": "IL-6 levels showed no increase when compared with NM, whereas the levels of IL-2, TNF-a, INF-, IL-10, and IL-17A did present a significant increase. It is well-known that, when there is an absence of cytokines, such as TNF-a, IL-12, or IFN-, the IL-6 cytokine can favor immune tolerance, in turn contributing to homeostasis [CITATION_1] . By contrast, as can be witnessed with other proinflammatory cytokines and in inflammatory conditions, IL-6 can aggravate the inflammatory disease pattern [CITATION_2] . Therefore, it can be proposed that the increased expression of IL-2, TNF-a, INF-, IL-10, and IL-17A cytokines can influence the role of IL-6, in turn causing alterations in host immune responses, thus contributing to the pathogenesis of CP.",
